    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-07-01T16:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-07-01T16:30:00-05:00" n="273"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d273">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">710.Consultation(2)/122: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Scott</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caracas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-01T17:00:00-04:30"
                            >July 1, 1940—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>99. Substance of Department’s circular telegrams of June 29, 4 p.m. and 6 p.m.
                    given Minister for Foreign Affairs,<note n="40" xml:id="d273fn1">Estebán Gil
                        Borges.</note> who states that it is doubtful if he can go to Havana.
                    However, if Secretary Hull goes and attendance of other Ministers of Foreign
                    Affairs seems slight, he will make every effort to go.</p>
                <pb facs="0221" n="209" xml:id="pg_209"/>
                <p>Revised agenda being studied and believed will be accepted by Venezuela without
                    changes. Venezuelan Embassy will be instructed by cable, July 3.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Scott</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
